title: Query regarding the exposed pp comm time
author: azharlightelligence

comments.body:
> > ```
> > //pp commtime
> >         Tick Expose_PP_time = (2 * vpp * GA * (pp_commsize * GBps / (param->net_work_param.pp) * 1e9) / FREQ );
> >         Expose_PP_time *= (1-param->net_work_param.pp_overlap_ratio) ;
> >         //pp bubble time
> >         pre_bubble_time *= static_cast<double>(PP_size - 1) / (GA * vpp);
> > ```
> > 
> > 
> >     
> >   
> > Dear SimAI team, thanks a lot for the excellent contribution. My question is regarding the exposed PP_time which has 2_vpp_GA factor. I totally understand that the prebubble_time is fine because it truly representing the bubble related time that needs to account for the single iteration time, the time other than this is spent on fwd + bwd . I also know that the GA is number of microbatches and vpp is the virtual pipeline states to improve the efficiency and reduce the bubble time. But only thing needs some clarification is the formula for exposed pp time. I also got the point that 2 accounts for pipeline comm : one of fwd and one for bwd. Please elaborate it thanks a lot once again
> 
> Is there any other question or concern?

My concern is that in this formula ``` Expose_PP_time = (2 * vpp * GA * (pp_commsize * GBps / (param->net_work_param.pp) * 1e9) / FREQ ); ``` the vpp*GA may be (PP_size-1). Because pp_commsize is already calculated and there are only PP_size-1 transfers for the PP, as PP comm is sequential, isnt it?

body: 框架层的调度器，只是把通信相关信息传给ns3吗？还是也会参与管理ns3中各类事件的调度吗？
author: jianglong-nie

comments.body:
> 框架层的调度器，只是把通信相关信息传给ns3吗？还是也会参与管理ns3中各类事件的调度吗？

两个调度器是有耦合关系的，框架层本身的调度逻辑被写入了ns-3事件中，调度过程又会调用新的ns-3事件

title: Hardware configuration
body: If I need to redevelop this code, are there any requirements for the hardware configuration?
author: HastyMonkey

comments.body:
> If I need to redevelop this code, are there any requirements for the hardware configuration?

Developing with SimAI doesn't require high-end specifications, an 8-core CPU with 16GB RAM should be sufficient. Of course, better configurations would be ideal (within a certain range, higher specs translate to faster NS-3 performance).

title: Unsupported weird communication type?
body:
Moe workload generated by AICB using the following command cannot be parsed:
```bash
sh scripts/megatron_gpt.sh \
--nnodes 1 --node_rank 0 --nproc_per_node 8 --master_addr localhost --master_port 29500 \
-m moe --world_size 8 --tensor_model_parallel_size 4 --pipeline_model_parallel 1 \
--moe_enable --expert_model_parallel_size 1  \
--frame Megatron --global_batch 16  \
--num_experts 4 --moe_router_topk 2 \
--micro_batch 1  --sp --grouped_gemm --aiob_enable --swiglu --use_flash_attn 
```

I suspect this is because the workload contains `ALLTOALL_EP` communication type, which cannot be parsed in Astrasim. So what's the difference between `ALLTOALL` and `ALLTOALL_EP` ? How to fix it?
author: maoshunyu

comments.body:
> Moe workload generated by AICB using the following command cannot be parsed:
> 
> ```shell
> sh scripts/megatron_gpt.sh \
> --nnodes 1 --node_rank 0 --nproc_per_node 8 --master_addr localhost --master_port 29500 \
> -m moe --world_size 8 --tensor_model_parallel_size 4 --pipeline_model_parallel 1 \
> --moe_enable --expert_model_parallel_size 1  \
> --frame Megatron --global_batch 16  \
> --num_experts 4 --moe_router_topk 2 \
> --micro_batch 1  --sp --grouped_gemm --aiob_enable --swiglu --use_flash_attn 
> ```
> 
> I suspect this is because the workload contains `ALLTOALL_EP` communication type, which cannot be parsed in Astrasim. So what's the difference between `ALLTOALL` and `ALLTOALL_EP` ? How to fix it?

ALLTOALL refers to the AlltoAll operation within a TP Group, while ALLTOALL_EP denotes the AlltoAll operation within an EP Group. Currently, only SimAI-Analytical supports the parsing of ALLTOALL_EP. You can try using the SimAI-Analytical tool for this purpose.
